All is now set for the publication of “Northern Professionals“, a calendar event by LEADERSHIP Newspapers Group. A statement by the management on Wednesday said Nigeria’s most Influential newspaper, would publish a compendium of distinguished Northern professionals on Monday, February 28, after which it would subsequently publish the list every four years. The maiden edition was published in 2013. According to the statement, this year’s edition has identified the professionals of northern extraction, who will be celebrated in a special series. “The purpose”, the statement said, “is to acknowledge the excellent work of these carefully selected professionals and to celebrate their worthy contributions to the region in particular and to the nation as a whole.” The profiles containing the achievements of these professionals would be distributed far and wide, and would also be pu lished online. The maiden edition contained persons like Datti Baba Ahmed, founder, Baze University; Engr Abdullahi Sule, the present Exe utive Governor of Nasarawa State; Alhaji Kabir Alkali Muhammed, former ICAN President; Sule man Yahyah, Dr Ahmed Tijani Mora, Dr Mohammed K Santuraki, Paul Orhii, Umar Ahmed Gana, among others. The statement further noted that the project champions are Rasheed Yusuf, Fadilah Sani Ismail  and Agbo Paul Augustine. 